Because of the unusual nature of the fair, Missouri State Fair Commissioners will be participating in a number of events daily beginning on August 10 as a whole or in small groups.  These events are primarily social in nature or for the purpose of supporting fair events and competitive winners (presenting awards, photo opportunities ...)   Tentatively, the Missouri State Fair Commission will meet in their Board Room daily August 11 - 21 to review previous day's events and receive scheduling information for the current day.  Generally, the time will be 8:30 a.m., but it is subject to change.  Members of public or media wanting to attend any of these scheduling sessions or review a schedule may contact Nancy Bouse (660-530-5603) for further information or to confirm the time.  Individuals with disabilities may contact Nancy Bouse (660-530-5603) for special assistance.
